Quality assurance body, Umalusi will brief the media on Friday morning on its preparedness to approve the release of the 2018 matric results. With just a week to go until the #MatricResults are released, Umalusi will this morning brief media on the approval of the national examination results in Pretoria. pic.twitter.com/S3kUlbIVjc — SA Gov News (@SAgovnews) December 28, 2018  Almost 800 000 learners sat for the final schooling year examination this year. Umalusi says the briefing is to inform the South African public about a very lengthy quality assurance process conducted by them to ensure the national examinations were conducted without any issues. WATCH RELATED VIDEO BELOW: 